  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1.jpg-2-1697119943517-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1.jpg-2-1697119943517-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1.jpg-2-1697119943517-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1.jpg-2-1697119943517-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1.jpg-2-1697119943517-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>halved</strong> <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 6-7 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-25-1697119908239-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-25-1697119908239-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-25-1697119908239-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-25-1697119908239-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-25-1697119908239-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[750ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>red lentils</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-27-1697119951201-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-27-1697119951201-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-27-1697119951201-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-27-1697119951201-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-27-1697119951201-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>rinsed lentils</strong> and <strong>chicken stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 15-18 min or until the lentils are almost tender</p><p>While the lentils are cooking, crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-26-1697119955187-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-26-1697119955187-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-26-1697119955187-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-26-1697119955187-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-26-1697119955187-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a lid with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat, add your <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>cardamom pods</strong> and <strong>star anise</strong> and cook for 1 min or until toasted</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>pilau rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-25-1697119958898-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-25-1697119958898-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-25-1697119958898-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-25-1697119958898-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-25-1697119958898-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, cut your <strong>free range chicken breast portions</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once the lentils are almost tender, add the <strong>chopped chicken</strong> and<strong> mango chutney </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 9-10 min further or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the lentils are tender</p><p>Once done, stir in the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>– this is your <strong>free range chicken & lentil dhansak</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-23-1697119962184-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-23-1697119962184-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-23-1697119962184-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-23-1697119962184-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-23-1697119962184-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges</p><p>Remove the <strong>star anise</strong> and <strong>cardamom pods</strong> from the<strong> </strong>pilau rice - this is your <strong>fragrant pilau rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-12-1697119965960-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-12-1697119965960-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-12-1697119965960-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-12-1697119965960-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-copy-12-1697119965960-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>free range chicken & lentil dhansak</strong> over the <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>pilau rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> and a <strong>lemon</strong> <strong>wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
